About GMP PRO

GMP PRO offers a set of advanced features in addition to GMP basic features.It requires a monthly subscription
GMP PRO focuses on the needs of educators. Features like Task, Help Request, Breakout rooms, Attendance, Control Panel, Stats and many other features are tailored for modern educators to run their online classrooms stress-free and more efficiently. Many educators, schools and school districts across the globe have subscribed to GMP PRO and reported great success in their virtual teaching.
We are offering 3 days free trial when you subscribe to GMP PRO, so that you can try out GMP PRO features before the subscription starts.
To subscribe, watch demo and find out more about GMP PRO, please click the link below for details

GMP PRO Feature - Breakout rooms
Users List (Assign or drag users to the rooms)
Feature Information
AIO stands for All-In-One. This is an experimental feature, It allows the meeting host to create multiple AIO breakout rooms within the current meeting without sending participants to another room. Breakout rooms participants will stay in the main room while they can only chat with and hear from their own group members. Please use the standard breakout rooms in case this approach doesn't work
Google Meet's microphone has been disabled for all participants as this feature uses its own microphone controls. The microphone will be restored automatically for all participants when the session ends. Click here if you want to change availability of Google Meet's microphone for participants.
It appears that there are existing AIO breakout room sessions still in progress. Please use button below to end all existing sessions
Users List (Assign or drag users to the rooms)
Maximum 10 participant per room

History (maximum 10 history records)

Saved Breakout Rooms configurations (maximum 10 history records)

Saved AIO Breakout Rooms configurations (maximum 10 history records)

Room Creation

Create breakout rooms - Select the number of breakout rooms you want, and click on "Create breakout room" button to create rooms. New rooms will be generated

Add one room - Add a new room to the existing list of rooms

Users assignment

You can drag and drop the user icons from Users List to any the section of any room, or click "Assign users randomly to rooms" button to assign users randomly. You can adjust the groups by dragging users between rooms

Main room's buttons

Room name - Room name is an editable field, you can assign a meaningful name to the room as you wish

Keep them here - Users will stay in the main room, and they will join the assigned breakout room in a new tab without leaving this room when you click 'Send'

Allow returning - Select this will give an option for breakout room users to return to the main room

Open for joining - The breakout room will be visible to join

"Timer" indicates when do you want to bring the users back to the main room from the breakout room automatically after they were sent to the room

"Send" button sends users to the breakout rooms they are assigned to. GMP will take users to their rooms

"Bring back" button brings the users back to the main room. GMP will bring users back to the main room

"Join" button opens a new tab and joins the specific breakout room automatically for you

"Focus" button switches your browser focus to the selected room instantly

"Message" button allows you to send a message to a specific breakout room

"Peek" button will show you the list of GMP users currently in the selected room

"Remove" button removes the breakout room from your room list, however, it does not close the room session

Send all, Bring back all, Join all and Message all buttons apply these actions to all the breakout rooms instead of a specific room.

"Copy rooms assignment" button copies these room assignment details, including room links and groups information to your clipboard, so that you can share with users in case you want them to join the rooms manually

Mute all - This will mute the audio of all joined breakout rooms

Save rooms configuration - Save the current configuration of rooms and users assignment. This configuration can be imported under the History tab

Breakout room's buttons

There are two buttons in the breakout room, docking on the left side of the screen. "Back" button allows user in a breakout room to go back to the main room. "Request to join" button sends a message with a link to the meeting host in the main room, requesting the meeting host to join the breakout room

History

Assignments and rooms history are captured when you click on "Send" button. The records can be downloaded as a text file

GMP PRO Feature - Talking stick

Talking stick feature gives the meeting host the ability to start a round of speaking as configured. The selected participants will have the microphone access in the arranged order while others listen with microphone muted. GMP will manage the speaking duration and microphone access of the participants automatically based on the configuration
Users List (Drag the name buttons to the Speakers section)
Speakers List  (Arrange the order of speaking by dragging the name buttons)
Each selected user will have microphone enabled for the duration selected while other users are muted
Please add speakers and select a duration before starting a session
